A concise way to see why the answer is 16 952 is as follows.  First, assign coordinates so that 1 sits at (0, 0), 2 at (1, 0), 3 at (1, 1), and so on, spiraling out in the usual “Ulam‐spiral” manner.  In that coordinate system:

• The number n lies on the “ring” k if max(|x|, |y|) = k.  
• The bottom‐right corner of ring k is (k, −k) and carries the number (2k + 1)².

Since 45² = 2025, the number 2025 is at the bottom‐right corner of ring 22, i.e. at (22, −22).  The next number, 2026, is then one step to the right, at (23, −22), which places 2026 on ring 23.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1) Neighbors on ring 22
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Ring 22 runs from 1850 up to 2025.  In particular:

 • (22, −22) is 2025, the bottom‐right corner of ring 22.  
 • (22, −21) is 1850, because ring 22 begins at (22, −21) = 1850 and ends at (22, −22) = 2025.

Thus the two ring‐22 neighbors of 2026 are  
(22, −22) → 2025 and  
(22, −21) → 1850.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2) Neighbors on ring 23
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Ring 23 has side length 47 and goes from 2026 up to 2209.  It starts at (23, −22) = 2026, goes upward 45 steps, then left 46, down 46, and right 46.  From that “path” one finds:

 • (23, −21) is 2027 (one step up from 2026).  
 • The corner (23, −23) is 2209 (the bottom‐right corner of ring 23).  
 • Hence just to its left, (22, −23), must be 2208.

So the three ring‐23 neighbors are  
(23, −21) → 2027,  
(23, −23) → 2209,  
(22, −23) → 2208.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3) Neighbors on ring 24
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Ring 24 has side length 49 and runs from 2210 to 2401.  It starts at (24, −23) = 2210 (one step right from 2209) and then moves up, left, down, and right.  Thus:

 • (24, −23) = 2210,  
 • (24, −22) = 2211 (the next step upward),  
 • (24, −21) = 2212.

These are the three ring‐24 neighbors of 2026.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
4) Summation
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Altogether, the eight neighbors of 2026 = (23, −22) and their values are:

 • Ring 22:  (22, −22) = 2025,   (22, −21) = 1850  
 • Ring 23:  (22, −23) = 2208,   (23, −23) = 2209,   (23, −21) = 2027  
 • Ring 24:  (24, −23) = 2210,   (24, −22) = 2211,   (24, −21) = 2212  

Their sum is  

2025 + 1850 + 2208 + 2209 + 2027 + 2210 + 2211 + 2212 = 16 952.

Hence, the required sum of the eight neighbors of 2026 in the spiral is 16 952.
